 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.370","title":"[audit][trace] Serialize TraceBufferHandle seq allocation with insertion","description":"Fix the shared TraceBufferHandle race where next_seq() and push_event() are split, allowing later events to overtake earlier sequence numbers under concurrency. Add a focused regression and migrate shared-handle emitters to an atomic record_event path.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CopperSpring","created_at":"2026-03-15T15:29:15.201772084Z","created_by":"CopperSpring","updated_at":"2026-03-15T15:34:10.547617087Z","closed_at":"2026-03-15T15:34:04.813747808Z","close_reason":"Implemented trace-ordering fix with focused regression and remote validation; remaining fmt/clippy failures are unrelated active-lane issues.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.370","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-15T15:29:15.201772084Z","created_by":"CopperSpring"}],"comments":[{"id":2514,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.370","author":"CopperSpring","text":"Implemented a trace-ordering race fix across shared TraceBufferHandle users. Added TraceBufferHandle::record_event(...) in src/trace/buffer.rs so sequence allocation and insertion happen under one critical section, added regression test trace_buffer_handle_record_event_serializes_seq_and_insertion, and migrated shared-handle emitters in runtime/state.rs, runtime/builder.rs, runtime/scheduler/worker.rs, cx/cx.rs, time/sleep.rs, lab/runtime.rs, and lab/scenario_runner.rs off the split next_seq()/push_event() pattern. Validation: rch exec -- cargo test -p asupersync trace_buffer_handle_record_event_serializes_seq_and_insertion --lib -- --nocapture ✅; rch exec -- cargo check --all-targets ✅; rch exec -- cargo fmt --check ❌ on unrelated pre-existing drift in src/transport/sink.rs; rch exec -- cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings ❌ on unrelated existing warnings in src/sync/rwlock.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-15T15:30:06Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.371","title":"[audit][service/load_balance] Zero-weight backends must stay unselectable during ready fallback","description":"Weighted documents that a backend with weight 0 is never selected, but LoadBalancer::call_balanced() linearly probes every backend after the initial strategy pick. If a positive-weight backend is pending and a zero-weight backend is ready, the fallback scan can dispatch to the zero-weight backend. Make fallback respect strategy-selectable indices and add a focused regression.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CopperSpring","created_at":"2026-03-15T15:40:08.358772295Z","created_by":"CopperSpring","updated_at":"2026-03-15T15:48:21.544628611Z","closed_at":"2026-03-15T15:48:21.115223299Z","close_reason":"Implemented zero-weight fallback guard and focused regressions; full cargo validation blocked by unrelated repo-frontier issues.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","load-balance","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.371","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-15T15:40:08.358772295Z","created_by":"CopperSpring"}],"comments":[{"id":2515,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.371","author":"CopperSpring","text":"Fixed LoadBalancer call_balanced so readiness fallback respects strategy-level backend eligibility instead of probing every backend indiscriminately. Added Strategy::permits_index() with a Weighted override that rejects zero-weight indices, then used it in the fallback scan. Added focused regressions lb_call_balanced_skips_zero_weight_ready_backend_during_weighted_fallback and lb_call_balanced_rejects_only_ready_zero_weight_backend in src/service/load_balance.rs. Local hygiene: rustfmt +nightly --edition 2024 src/service/load_balance.rs passed; git diff --check -- src/service/load_balance.rs passed. Validation via rch: focused cargo test -p asupersync zero_weight_backend --lib -- --nocapture was blocked by unrelated compile errors in src/io/browser_stream.rs; broad cargo check --all-targets was blocked by unrelated compile errors in tests/security_invariants.rs and src/channel/mpsc.rs; cargo fmt --check reported unrelated existing drift in asupersync-tokio-compat/src/tower_bridge.rs, src/channel/mpsc.rs, src/combinator/timeout.rs, src/distributed/encoding.rs, src/lab/runtime.rs, and tests/wasm_browser_feasibility_matrix.rs; one cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings attempt was tainted by an rch worker temp-dir failure and is not counted.","created_at":"2026-03-15T15:48:09Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.372","title":"[audit][typed-symbol] TypedDecoder::decode_from_stream must stop on object completion","description":"Focused audit child for src/types/typed_symbol.rs only. TypedDecoder::decode_from_stream() currently buffers symbols until stream EOF and only then calls decode(), so a long-lived stream carrying one decodable object followed by later traffic or just Pending will never return once the first object is complete. Scope: make stream decoding return as soon as one typed object has enough symbols to reconstruct, keep metadata/type validation fail-closed, add focused regression coverage for completion-before-EOF, and validate with rch-backed cargo gates plus local hygiene.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaCliff","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-15T16:00:32.520071088Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-15T16:27:08.261195529Z","closed_at":"2026-03-15T16:27:08.261171595Z","close_reason":"Completed: TypedDecoder::decode_from_stream now returns on object completion and has regression coverage for completion-before-EOF.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.372","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-15T16:00:32.520071088Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
