+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.373","title":"[audit][websocket] Reject invalid close codes and UTF-8 reasons on decode","description":"Fresh-eyes audit follow-up for src/net/websocket/frame.rs. The decode path currently rejects only the 1-byte Close payload case, but RFC 6455 also requires inbound Close frames to reject unsendable/invalid status codes and non-UTF-8 reason strings. Patch decode-time validation and add focused regression tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BronzeBrook","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:19:08.504942899Z","created_by":"BronzeBrook","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:35:21.624442715Z","closed_at":"2026-03-16T04:35:20.294752966Z","close_reason":"Completed: fail-closed websocket close-frame decode validation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","net","protocol","websocket"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.373","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:19:08.504942899Z","created_by":"BronzeBrook"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.374","title":"[audit][grpc] Make Channel::connect fail closed for non-loopback URIs","description":"src/grpc/client.rs currently accepts arbitrary http:// and https:// channel URIs in Channel::connect_with_config(), but the client implementation is still loopback-only: connect_with_config() only validates/stores the URI and GrpcClient::build_outbound_metadata() stamps x-asupersync-grpc-transport=loopback. This makes Channel::connect(\"http://real-host:50051\") look like a real network connection even though no transport exists. Fail closed by rejecting non-loopback targets until a real transport is implemented, add focused regressions for accepted loopback hosts and rejected remote hosts, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","notes":"Implemented in src/grpc/client.rs and supporting grpc docs/tests. Channel::connect(_with_config) now rejects non-loopback hosts so the in-memory loopback transport fails closed instead of pretending to connect to arbitrary remote targets. Updated grpc module/client docs to state the loopback-only contract and switched affected grpc tests to http://loopback:50051 or loopback host variants. Validation: cargo fmt --check on touched files passed locally; rch exec targeted tests passed for grpc::client::tests::channel_connect_rejects_non_loopback_host and grpc_verify_036_channel_builder; rch exec cargo check -p asupersync --tests passed; broad rch clippy -p asupersync --lib --tests -- -D warnings is currently blocked by unrelated pre-existing clippy::uninlined_format_args violations in tests/wasm_qa_evidence_matrix_contract.rs.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"NavyHarbor","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:28:14.222404956Z","created_by":"NavyHarbor","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:29:26.878848974Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","grpc"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.374","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:28:14.222404956Z","created_by":"NavyHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.38","title":"[audit][rate_limit] Restore consumed rate-limit token if guarded operation or web handler panics","description":"Both the core combinator and the sync web adapter consume a rate-limit token before invoking user code. In src/combinator/rate_limit.rs, RateLimiter::call_weighted() acquires tokens and then runs op() without an unwind guard, so a synchronous panic burns tokens even though the operation never completed. In src/web/middleware.rs, RateLimitMiddleware::call() uses limiter.try_acquire() and then calls the inner handler directly, so a panicking handler leaks the consumed token in the same way. Add a narrow refund path for panic unwind, route the web middleware through the panic-safe helper, add focused regression coverage in both modules, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkForest","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:29:33.537070930Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:50:02.362203392Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:50:02.362173717Z","close_reason":"Refund consumed rate-limit tokens on synchronous panic in combinator and web middleware; focused rch regressions passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","combinator","rate-limit","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.38","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:29:33.537070930Z","created_by":"PinkForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","title":"[audit][grpc] Make tracing interceptor request IDs deterministic","description":"src/grpc/interceptor.rs currently generates x-request-id values from SystemTime::now(), which makes request IDs nondeterministic and introduces ambient wall-clock authority into library code. Replace that clock-based ID generation with a deterministic interceptor-owned source, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaHollow","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:30:28.727934377Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:38.909958605Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:38.909932226Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","grpc"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:30:28.727934377Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2460,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Replaced TracingInterceptor request ID generation in src/grpc/interceptor.rs with a deterministic interceptor-owned AtomicU64 counter shared across clones, preserving caller-supplied x-request-id values and removing ambient SystemTime usage. Added focused regressions tracing_interceptor_uses_deterministic_sequential_ids and tracing_interceptor_preserves_existing_request_id. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/grpc/interceptor.rs ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-clippy cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-test cargo test -p asupersync --lib tracing_interceptor_ -- --nocapture ✅ (3 passed).","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:32Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.4","title":"[audit][service] Reserve buffer capacity in poll_ready so clone races cannot revoke readiness","description":"Buffer::poll_ready currently reports Ready based only on the shared pending count, but it does not actually reserve a slot. Two clones can both observe Ready against capacity=1, after which one caller can fill the buffer and make the other caller's immediately-following call() fail with BufferError::Full. That violates the usual Service contract expectation that a successful poll_ready authorizes the next call on that handle. Fix by reserving a slot during poll_ready, consuming it in call(), releasing it on drop/close, and adding clone-race regression tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CloudyPond","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:50:03.548796130Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T02:08:16.874795269Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T02:08:16.874685616Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","buffer","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:50:03.548796130Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
@@ -2659,6 +2660,8 @@
 {"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.29","title":"[RaptorQ] Make Symbol::new_for_test source-by-default and add explicit repair helper","description":"# Summary\n`Symbol::new_for_test(object, sbn, esi, data)` currently infers `SymbolKind` as `Source` only for `esi == 0` and `Repair` otherwise. That is not a valid RaptorQ rule because source-vs-repair depends on block K, not on whether ESI equals zero.\n\n# Why this is a bug\nMany tests use `new_for_test` as a generic symbol constructor for ordered source-like sequences (`esi = 0,1,2,...`). The current helper silently misclassifies every nonzero ESI as repair, which can distort `SymbolSet` accounting and any other test logic that inspects symbol kind.\n\n# Plan\n- make the default helper construct a source symbol\n- add an explicit repair-specific test helper\n- update only the call sites that truly need repair-kind semantics\n- validate affected surfaces with `rch exec -- ...` cargo commands\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BronzeBrook","created_at":"2026-03-16T03:28:08.827378068Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-16T03:39:03.440520243Z","closed_at":"2026-03-16T03:39:03.440483695Z","close_reason":"Completed: default source helper + explicit repair helper + SymbolSet regression coverage","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.29","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T03:28:08.827378068Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.3","title":"[compile-frontier] Fix race/laws/three_lane cargo check failures","description":"Resolve rch cargo check --all-targets blockers: stray doc-comment item error in src/combinator/race.rs, E0282 inference failures in src/combinator/laws.rs test assertions, and missing should_skip_backoff_timeout_park symbol in src/runtime/scheduler/three_lane.rs tests. Include rch-offloaded validation.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PurpleBrook","estimated_minutes":75,"created_at":"2026-03-05T01:59:32.890484965Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-05T02:08:34.071035084Z","closed_at":"2026-03-05T02:08:34.062811192Z","close_reason":"Superseded by concurrent fixes: rch cargo check --all-targets now passes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["combinator","compile","runtime","unblock"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.3","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T01:59:32.890484965Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.30","title":"Fix cumulative multi-block decode progress accounting","description":"Implemented cumulative symbol accounting in DecodingPipeline progress/error reporting after completed blocks are cleared from SymbolSet; added focused regression coverage in src/decoding.rs. Validation: rch-wrapped cargo fmt --check and cargo check --all-targets passed. Remaining lib-test/clippy failures are pre-existing unrelated Worker trace exhaustiveness errors outside the reserved slice.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"GreenCat","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:02:16.934102023Z","created_by":"GreenCat","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:02:16.934102023Z","closed_at":"2026-03-16T04:02:16.934102023Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["correctness","decoding","raptorq"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.30","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:02:16.934102023Z","created_by":"GreenCat"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.31","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][encoding] Reject invalid config even for empty payloads","description":"EncodingPipeline::plan_blocks() currently returns early for empty input before validating symbol_size, max_block_size, repair_overhead, and pool/config consistency. That lets encode(&[]) silently accept invalid encoder configuration instead of failing closed. Scope: factor config validation so empty payloads reject invalid config just like non-empty payloads, add focused inline regressions in src/encoding.rs, and validate with rch-backed focused cargo test/check commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CyanOwl","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:24:42.039750613Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:29:55.181110110Z","closed_at":"2026-03-16T04:29:53.550464900Z","close_reason":"Patched src/encoding.rs so empty payloads no longer bypass invalid encoder config; added three focused regressions; rustfmt --check src/encoding.rs passed; rch-wrapped cargo check -p asupersync --lib passed; rch-wrapped cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings passed; rch-wrapped cargo test -p asupersync --lib empty_payload_still_rejects -- --nocapture passed (3 tests).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["correctness","encoding","raptorq"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.31","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:24:42.039750613Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.32","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][params] Prevent next_prime_ge overflow wraparound near usize::MAX","description":"Focused follow-up under the top-level RaptorQ epic. In src/raptorq/rfc6330.rs, next_prime_ge() uses unchecked `n + 1` / `candidate += 2` arithmetic and is_prime() uses unchecked `d * d`, so overflow-adjacent inputs can panic in debug or wrap in release and return a prime smaller than the requested lower bound. Scope: make the prime search fail closed instead of wrapping near usize::MAX, harden primality iteration against multiplication overflow, preserve normal cases like `18 -> 19`, and add focused regressions in the same file.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ChartreuseDune","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:28:50.061131491Z","created_by":"ChartreuseDune","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:29:01.334916928Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["correctness","raptorq","rfc6330"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.32","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:28:50.061131491Z","created_by":"ChartreuseDune"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.4","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][systematic] Eliminate small-K encoder singularity workaround and tighten recovery invariants","description":"Focused child slice under asupersync-2c9j7. Confirm whether the small-K SystematicEncoder singularity workaround in src/raptorq/systematic.rs is still masking a live defect or stale scaffolding. If live, fix the systematic/constraint path so encoder construction and in-scope recovery no longer depend on seed retries or tolerated SingularMatrix outcomes. If stale, remove the workaround and harden the regression coverage so conformance tests fail closed instead of accepting singularity in supported regimes.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"LavenderFalcon","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:16:59.056800493Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T03:28:48.183478822Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T03:28:48.183455909Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","raptorq","systematic"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:16:59.056800493Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-2c9j7.5","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][decoder] Classify rank-deficient dense-core failures as singular, not insufficient_symbols","description":"Focused child slice under asupersync-2c9j7. InactivationDecoder currently returns DecodeError::InsufficientSymbols from the dense-core elimination path when n_rows < n_cols after peeling/inactivation, even if the caller supplied at least L received symbols and the real issue is rank deficiency/redundancy (for example duplicate or linearly dependent equations). That misclassifies decoder failure semantics, can distort retry/governance logic, and weakens conformance evidence. Scope: restore a deterministic rank-deficiency classification for this path, add focused regressions proving duplicate/redundant inputs fail as singular rather than underprovisioned, and validate with rch-backed cargo gates.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"EmeraldForge","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:32:53.258860614Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T03:51:28.212834675Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T03:51:28.212812574Z","close_reason":"Completed: dense-core underdetermined failures now classify as SingularMatrix, duplicate-ESI regression tightened, targeted rch tests and lib check passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2c9j7.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2c9j7","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T03:32:53.258860614Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
