 {"id":"asupersync-2cvac","title":"[FOUNDATION] franken_decision crate — Decision Contract Schema and Runtime","description":"Implement the franken_decision crate that defines the canonical Decision Contract infrastructure used across ALL FrankenSuite projects. This crate is the third leg of the foundation tripod (franken_kernel types, franken_evidence ledger, franken_decision contracts). MOTIVATION: Currently, Decision Contracts exist only in the methodology bead (bd-1e2if.6) and are scheduler-specific. But Decision Contracts are a cross-cutting concern -- every FrankenSuite project that makes runtime decisions must use the same contract schema. SCOPE: (1) DecisionContract trait: state_space(), action_set(), loss_matrix(), update_posterior(), choose_action(), fallback_action(). (2) LossMatrix<S,A> struct: indexed by (state, action) pairs, non-negative values, serializable to/from TOML. (3) Posterior struct: probability distribution over states, must sum to 1.0. (4) FallbackPolicy: calibration drift threshold, e-process breach, confidence interval width triggers. (5) DecisionAuditEntry: links to EvidenceLedger for structured audit records. DEPENDENCIES: Depends on franken_kernel (TraceId, DecisionId, Cx) and franken_evidence (EvidenceLedger). TRACING SPEC: Span: decision::evaluate with decision_id, contract_name. INFO log: decision made (action, expected_loss, calibration, fallback). WARN log: calibration drift detected. ERROR log: e-process breach. DEBUG log: posterior update details. Metrics: decision_latency_us (histogram), fallback_active_total (counter), calibration_score (gauge). ACCEPTANCE: DecisionContract implementable in <50 lines, LossMatrix supports TOML reconfig, posterior update O(|S|) no alloc, decision latency <5us, all decisions auditable via EvidenceLedger.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T17:58:53.293386490Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T19:21:31.888783018Z","closed_at":"2026-02-13T19:2