-{"id":"asupersync-2cyx5.1","title":"[RAPTORQ-RFC6330][G2] Serialize real gate/comparator NDJSON emitters and test production output","description":"Focused follow-up under Track-G. In tests/ci_regression_gates.rs, the production G2 emitters hand-build NDJSON via raw string interpolation, but the current schema-compliance test validates a separate handcrafted sample instead of the real formatter. That means quotes, backslashes, or newlines in emitted string fields (scenario_id, policy_reason, policy_replay_ref, regime/policy mode) can corrupt the actual log into invalid JSON while tests still pass. Scope: replace manual JSON assembly with a serde-backed/pure formatter shared by the gate and comparator emitters, add a regression proving the real emitted line parses correctly with escaped string content, and validate through rch-backed focused gates plus required hygiene checks.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ChartreuseDune","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:15:00.658047679Z","created_by":"ChartreuseDune","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:15:00.658047679Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ci","governance","raptorq","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2cyx5.1","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2cyx5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:15:00.658047679Z","created_by":"ChartreuseDune"}]}
